Ord River Hydro Power Station is a hydroelectric power station on the Ord River in Western Australia. It has four turbines, with a generating capacity of 30 megawatts (40,000 hp) of electricity.
The power station was completed in April 1997, with four 7.5 megawatts (10,100 hp) turbines. It supplies electricity to the nearby Argyle diamond mine, and the towns of Kununurra and Wyndham.
